Noblesse Luxe PublishingEXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW                                                            Tessa Williams                                                  CULT PERFUMES                                                  The Book & Exclusive Interview        It gives me great pleasure to introduce a book that I admired since the first glance at its description while searching for book on fragrances that I may have missed.       The title, CULT PERFUMES- The World's Most Exclusive Perfumeries published by MERRELL gave me goose bumps. It was intriguing and a little bit of a mystery to find out what perfumeries the author thought were exclusive.       Tessa Williams is a journalist and has written for several well known publications such as Vogue, Marie Claire, Elle, The Times, just to name a few. I immediately assumed Ms. Williams knew what she is talking about because those publications only work with the best and most knowledgeable writers.      I admire the extensive research done for this book and for Ms.Williams taking the time and expense to visit over 25 perfumeries to conduct interviews with the perfumers, and get a behind the scene look at these beloved perfumeries that have reached the noses and hearts of millions of people around the world.     Not only is the research detailed by CULT PERFUMES offers beautiful photos of the perfumeries, the perfumes and of the perfumers. So, you get a package deal with this book.   The layout and understanding of each perfumery in CULT PERFUMES is easy reading with details that gives historical background starting with Ancient Egypt to the master perfumeries of the twentieth and twenty-first centuries.  If you are new to niche perfumery, Welcome...CULT PERFUMES-The World's Most Exclusive Perfumeries is a excellent place to start.  I am deeply honored and privileged to have Tessa Williams, author of CULT PERFUMES-The World's Most Exclusive Perfumeries answer my questions about this beautifully orchestrated book of my most favorite fragrances.                              THE INTERVIEW1. Tessa, did you write Cult Perfumes: The World's Most Exclusive Perfumeries because you felt this type of book and subject matter is missing from the fragrance industry?I wrote the book that I wanted to read and there is certainly no other book like this around about fragrances.I’ve always been fascinated by perfume, even as a young girl, each scent I knew began to unravel a different story for me.I wanted to write a book about perfume, and initially I had a different idea,this was similar but slightly different and the publisher liked this so this was how the book evolved.2. The book is so beautifully arranged. Did you arrange the layout of pictures and articles yourself or did you have help?I was lucky to have worked with an amazingly talented team at Merrell.My Editor there, Claire Chandler was a terrific help and the Art Director, Nicola Bailey had this incredible artistic vision for a very beautiful book . Sadly they have now departed towork at various other companies as the publishing company is no longer as diverse.3. During your interviews with the perfumers, what would you say is the most common in terms of their passion for perfumery?I came across undying passion amongst the perfumers that I met. The most uniting theme seemed to be that most people were creating their unique and special perfumes for love of creation than from mere commercial desire to make something that sold in the wider sphere.4. Tessa, how time consuming was it preparing to write CULT PERFUMES: The World's Most Exclusive Perfumeries?The whole process probably took around 2 years -The research was a wonderful journey for me, taking me to meet such special perfumers all around the world, from the magical Serge Lutens in Paris to being present at the 400th anniversary party of Santa Maria Novella in Florence.Whenever possible I made the journey to meet people personally as I wanted the book to reflect this authenticity and connect with the perfumers on a one to one basis. I did face to face interviews with many key fragrance creators, which took a lot of time, probably about a year , compiling them all and travelling to each place.Roja Dove , a real character , Francis Kurkdjian, a fascinating and very likable Parisian, Jo Malone, a very business like and rather tough but friendly lady, Antonia Bellanca (creator of Antonia’s Flowers) wonderfully passionate and inspiring Italian/ American .After months of travels and many telephone and Skype interviewsit then took hour upon hour of sitting writing on the computer, into the night and starting early in the morning.I was lucky that my family , also writers and artists were especially encouraging to me at this time. My father used to ask me every day how many words I had written - that really helped - Also working with a fantastic Editor who insisted on deadlines being met and would not allow for much procrastination. My daughter too was very helpfulan

My Brush Collection: Part One – Favorite Foundation Brushes (Hakuhodo & Koyudo) I Bought This
 
Last year, I turned into a full-on makeup brush snob. I decided to save up some money, then find and buy the absolute best brushes I could get my hands on, no matter where in the world those brushes might be. It turns out they were in Japan – Hakuhodo, Koyudo, Chikuhodo – it seemed all the greats originated from Kumano, a town adjacent to Hiroshima with a centuries long tradition of creating the finest, handmade, artisan brushes in the world. Since that realization, I’ve acquired a respectable number of magnificent Japanese brushes. I’m really proud of my collection, which is openly displayed on the antique desk in my bedroom. No matter how many times I walk past them, I still get excited every time I catch a glimpse. Today is the first installment of a three part series that will highlight my favorite performers, and I’ve decided to kick things off with the foundation brush category.
My favorite foundation brushes, engaged in a group hug.
For years I assumed I was made to be a finger applicator when it came to foundation. I hated paddle brushes, which have somehow become the standard for foundation brushes. At some point I acquired the large, fluffy, Tarte foundation brush, which is how I learned that foundation brushes don’t have to suck. I then obtained a few Sigma brushes from the Kabuki collection, which also performed well. The Tarte and Sigma brushes aren’t high enough on my list to be called favorites exactly, but they will always have a special place in my heart – they taught me that not all foundation brushes are paddle-shaped pieces of crap, and filled my sails with the wind I needed to venture on my epic quest for The World’s Best Makeup Brushes.
The first brushes to save me from paddle brushes.
I might be overselling the quest part. I didn’t sail a ship to Japan. I just got online and ordered myself a few Hakuhado brushes I’d been researching. Yay, global commerce! Of the Japanese artisan brush companies, Hakuhodo is probably the most well-known. They even have a distribution center in California, which is where all the US orders are shipped from. The brushes are still made in Japan, however, in the Kumano-based facility where each piece is still handmade, and every natural hair still uncut.
Hakuhodo G5557
My Hakuhodo foundation brush is the G5557. This is a full, round, angled brush primarily comprised of soft goat hair. It also contains synthetic fibers that are carefully arranged and extend just 2mm past the tips of the goat hair, making this brush a sort of primo duo-fibre. The longest side of the brush head measures about an inch (26mm), and the diameter is about the size of a poker chip. It performs unbelievably well with cream and liquid foundations, but the thicker foundations is where this brush really shines. It’s always the brush I reach for anytime I’m wearing something like Kat Von D Lock-it Tattoo Foundation, which has a particularly dense formula. It also works well with thinner liquids, such as the Urban Decay Naked Foundation and Chanel Perfection Lumiere. The finish is always even, smooth, and looks airbrushed. (Oh dear. I just realized this could get a bit tiresome – all of my favorite foundation brushes impart an even, smooth, airbrushed look. That’s why they’re my favorites. )
Hakuhodo G5557
Hakuhodo G5557
Hakuhodo G5557
 
Koyudo Fu-Pa Series
It was my search for Hakuhodo brush reviews that led me to two wonderful discoveries . One of those discoveries was Koyudo, a small, Japanese artisan brush company also located in the legendary Kumano. The other discovery was the website that led me to Koyudo, a blog called “Sweet Makeup Temptations,” which heavily features photos and reviews for a huge variety of high-end and artisan makeup brushes. If you are at all interested in makeup brushes, Sweet Makeup Temptations will be your new pornography.
The Koyudo Fu-Pa series is what grabbed my attention first. I had never (and still haven’t) seen any makeup brushes like these before. They’re short and stocky, measuring anywhere from 3.5 to 4 inches, end-to-end. Each one is very, very, densely packed with carefully arranged, extremely soft, natural hair. The structure and shape of the brush heads are perfection – no weird dents, or irregularities to be found in any of the Fu-Pa brushes. I love how unique they look – they’re cute without being childish. But even more than the way they look, I love how they perform.
Koyudo Fu-Pa SeriesLeft to right: Fu-Pa02, FuPa01, Fu-Pa14
The Koyudo Fu-Pa01 is labeled as a cheek brush, but I actually use this brush for powder foundation. The dense, tightly packed, soft Sokoho goat hair, rounded shape, and short handle all work together to make the perfect tool for applying and buffing mineral makeup and pressed powder foundations. I really liked the palette, and I think that the majority of the shades applied well over bare skin and lasted for seven to eight hours before creasing and/or fading.  The pigmentation was typically good with soft, blendable textures that were easy to work with.  This palette is all shimmer, though, so if you like satins and mattes to vary the finishes that you use, you’ll need to incorporate another palette. Hace tres años soñábamos con crear en @chicasguapastv un espacio para inspirarnos, descubrir nuevos talentos y acercarnos a nuestras marcas ... una forma humana y real. Así como terminamos amigas de Anna @fendi, entrevistar a @thierrywasser nos acercó al universo de @guerlain de una forma sincera y honesta. Como la relación que mantiene la firma hace tres generaciones con sus proveedores de las rosas de Bulgaria ; la elección de Angelina Jolie como musa de #MonGuerlain por su compromiso humanitario; y la invitación a que "Mon Guerlain, sea tú Guerlain", apropiándote de la maravillosa aura que irradia la fragancia para sentirnos fuertes y seguras con nosotras mismas. Porque para Thierry ... A seguir trabajando, soñando y apostando por hacer algo distinto y animarnos a dejar nuestra huella  ¡Bonjour #ChicaGuapa!

Quattro serate all'insegna della bellezza, alla scoperta della nuova fragranza Guerlain.Mon Guerlain ti invita a celebrare il nuovo profumo della Maison durante quattro eventi esclusivi realizzati in collaborazione con Grazia.it e Sephora, dove potrai vivere un percorso olfattivo emozionale alla scoperta delle note della fragranza.A celebrazione della donna moderna, Mon Guerlain ne esalta la femminilità, fatta di molteplici sfaccettature ed emozioni che la rendono unica: la sua forza e la sua ... verso gli altri. Una donna dal fascino ammaliante, impersonificata da Angelina Jolie.Durante le serate sarà possibile ricevere un welcome gift Guerlain, un flash make up personalizzato, un tattoo oro e immortalare il ricordo dell'evento con una foto, com'è già avvenuto a ... giovedì 6 aprile, presso il Beauty Store Sephora di via del Corso. L'evento è stato un successo, per scoprire l'universo Mon Guerlain e la sua nuova fragranza, vai sul sito  e seleziona la tua data e città, avrai tutti i dettagli dei prossimi ... Samsara by Jean-Paul Guerlain for Guerlain 1989 .
Portia
.
Hello lovelies,
Samsara has great memories for me of my Mum. I bought her some one year and she wore it often. It’s weird but I rarely hear people speak of this particular Guerlain, it’s still in department stores so must be a good seller for them. Every now & then I get mine out to reminisce. Then I wonder why I don’t wear it more.
Samsara by Guerlain 1989
Samsara by Jean-Paul Guerlain
Fragrantica
Fragrantica gives these featured accords:
Top: Bergamot, lemon, ylang-ylang, peach, green notes
Heart: Jasmine, iris, narcissus, violet, rose
Base: Sandalwood, vanilla, tonka bean, amber, musk
Samsara means “Wheel Of Life” in Sanskrit according to Jean-Paul Guerlain the perfumes main creator.
Creamy tropical flowers and fruit, a little sharp in the open. Samsara doesn’t take long to ... what I wanted to do as a life hobby.

BLACK IS THE NEW BLACK
In 2017, Guerlain has launched three fragrances featured in black bottles. In colour psychology, black is associated with power, authority, prestige, formality, elegance, ... mystery. Black is therefore an effective marketing tool in the beauty and fashion industries. Except for La Petite Robe Noire, Guerlain hasn’t created many fragrances with the word "black" or "noir" included in the name, however, the brand has had its fair share of black bottles. THIERRY WASSER: EXPLORADOR EN ESENCIA Un poco más de la historia detrás de Mon Guerlain, la nueva fragancia creada por Thierry Wasser, el sucesor de Jean-Paul Guerlain.

––––

 
De nuestra edición de mayo, continuamos con la entrevista a Thierry Wasser respecto al lanzamiento del año de Guerlain.
 
Por Daniela Vega

 
El nacimiento de una fragancia en manos de Thierry Wasser es un camino de intuición, expertise, dedicación y mucho corazón. “La inspiración puede ser conocer a alguien, una idea simple. Nuestra nueva fragancia Mon Guerlain presenta a Angelina Jolie como musa, pero cuando comencé a pensar en esa fragancia, Angelina no estaba en el mapa. ... creatividad no necesita mucha atención, es solo un detalle que dispara tu mente al modo creativo. En 190 años (de Guerlain) hemos estado al lado de las mujeres en su lucha por derechos, es algo importante que quiero plasmar en el ... ingredientes, tengo que escogerlos muy bien para plasmar ese retrato del que te hablo”.
 
Sobre el nacimiento de Mon Guerlain…
“En estos viajes de búsqueda de ingredientes es cuando las flores te hablan. Por ejemplo, al sur de Francia descubrí ... es una nota simple y su simplicidad me hizo sentir verdadero y por eso elegí esa lavanda para comenzar Mon Guerlain, no solo por su frescura sino por su autenticidad. Las mujeres se acercan a la marca de manera auténtica”.

¡Los míticos Météorites de Guerlain cumplen 30 años! En 1987 nacía uno de los más aplaudidos productos de belleza en la historia del maquillaje. Dominique Szabo, Directora Creativa de Guerlain en la época, quería ofrecer a las mujeres una luminosidad natural inigualable, corrigiendo y sublimando la piel gracias a un ... reinventándose en cada colección. Un objeto de deseo para toda beauty lover que sigue llevando su emblemático aroma de violetas. Guerlain lanza una colección especial para celebrar el aniversario de su producto más mítico.30 años de luminosidad natural y de corrección ... aportar a las mujeres una luminosidad natural que corrigiera la piel sin sobrecargarla. Basándose en los principios de la colorimetría, Guerlain creó 3 armonías de color para cubrir las necesidades de las pieles claras, medias y doradas, compuesta cada una por ... el complemento perfecto para aplicar las perlas míticas de la firma. Su precio 40,30€.¿Sois fans de los emblemáticos Météorites de Guerlain? ¿Qué os parece la colección 30 aniversario?

Guerlain Terracotta Chic Tropic Estate 2017 Guerlain Terracotta Chic Tropic è il consueto appuntamento annuale con la tanto attesa edizione limitata estiva della terra Terracotta. Si tratta ... di bergamotto e mandarino, unito all’aroma floreale di Gardenia ed Ylang Ylang, fresco e frizzante, perfetto per la stagione calda.
Guerlain Terracotta Chic Tropic Estate 2017

La terra si presenta in una gradevole scatolina in latta ed un maxi formato da ... ben 18 gr.
All’interno, la cialda è finemente decorata con motivi bronzei dorati ravvivati da un tocco di pesca corallo.
Guerlain Terracotta Chic Tropic può essere utilizzata sia come terra che come blush. Aiuta a ravvivare il naturale colorito della pelle ... pigmenti dorati e bellissimi inserti color pesca.

Il prodotto, proposto in edizione limitata, si può acquistare nelle migliori profumerie concessionarie Guerlain.
Per maggiori informazioni sul brand consultare il sito ufficiale.

NATURAL BORN UNISEX
Guerlain's vintage perfume art contains several elements that give it its renowned unisex touch, but maybe the single most characteristic feature in that regard is the consistent use of aromatics and citrusy notes. Guerlain's fresh and aromatic profile goes back to Aimé Guerlain’s Jicky (1889), and before that to the great cologne era of Pierre-François-Pascal Guerlain. In fact, Jicky is an assembly of Eau de Cologne Impériale and a base of vanillin, coumarin, balsams, sandalwood, and animalic notes. Jacques Guerlain in particular was known for his fresh top notes. If Jacques Guerlain were a chef, citrus and aromatics would be his dash of salt and pinch of pepper, and many of his perfumes would today be considered as men's scents. For a Jean-Paul Guerlain version, try his Héritage from 1992. In keeping with the Guerlain tradition of choosing three-syllable names, Héritage is more than apt as it also harks back to his predecessors’ recipes, replete with Provençal herbs and warm, oriental notes.

GUERLAIN | Mon Guerlain Fragrance REVIEWEarlier this spring, the house of Guerlain introduced a new fragrance to its core lineup - Mon Guerlain* was created to represent new modern femininity. To be honest, I had been waiting for years for Guerlain to launch a true power scent as its recent releases seemed lackluster and felt more like fillers with its attempt ... does so in a sophisticated and grown up way. It reminds me of My Burberry Black but done up in Guerlain tradition; a little softer, grounded and honest. SHOP GUERLAIN | Sephora | The Bay (50ml @ $119)On my skin, Mon Guerlain pulls a little powdery and musky with a definite flower overtone. A morning application will last me the entire day ... I can't call it a favourite. Despite not being a frequent wearer of orientals, my signature scent is actually a Guerlain classic with a very similar profile and while I desperately wanted to love this as a modern take - it ... a figment of my imagination but either way, it won't be a replacement anytime soon. For those who are encountering Guerlain for the firs time, this could very well be your new stand by.Take care, Twitter | Youtube | Instagram |

Batom Rouge G da Guerlain Hoje a resenha é puro luxo, vou falar sobre o Batom Rouge G da Guerlain.

Ganhei esse batom do Toni David de aniversário. Primeiro, achei loucura dele comprar um batom de 230 reais. Aí fui ler sobre o batom e vi tudo que ele fazia.

O Batom Rouge G De Guerlain é inspirado nas bolsas dos anos 30, que as mulheres usavam para deleitar suas maquiagens como se fossem preciosas joias. ... microesferas de ácido hialurônico preenchem as linhas finas e aumentam o desenho dos lábios. A vitamina A presente neste batom Guerlain estimula o crescimento das células epidérmicas aumentando a síntese das fibras de colágeno. Para intensificar as tonalidades possui pó de ... brilho desejado, a partir dessa pedra preciosa que representa um símbolo sagrado de pureza e amor.

 
Batom Rouge G da Guerlain, o que achei?
Pra começar, a embalagem é a coisa mais linda, realmente parece uma joia. Só achei meio pesada, ... de hidratação dele é maravilhoso, os lábios ficam super macios. Melhor que muito lip balm famoso.
Resumindo, o batom da Guerlain é muuuuito caro , mas é perfeito. Lindo, dura nos lábios e é super confortável, além da embalagem ser apaixonante. Item de luxo que vale a pena ter na vida.
O post Batom Rouge G da Guerlain apareceu primeiro em Karin França.

Guerlain Shalimar Parfum Initial Eau De Parfum Review Hi ladies,
I am mad about perfumes (who isn’t?). Recently, I went to ... buying a perfume; but I didn’t even knew what kind of fragrance I was searching for. When I checked out Guerlain Shalimar Parfum Initial Eau De Parfum, I knew this was the fragrance I was searching for. Here’s the review of ... in perfumery embodies skin-caressing sensuality with a hint of the forbidden. “Wearing Shalimar means letting your senses take over,” Jacques Guerlain would say.

My Experience with Guerlain Shalimar Parfum Initial Eau De Parfum:
It comes in a very beautiful glass bottle with Shalimar written on it in blue color. It has a blue cap with Guerlain Paris written on it. The shape of the bottle is what attracted me to it first.

Fragrance:
Top Notes-Bergamot,Orange,Green notes. ... long way. Staying power is very good. I personally started loving it once I got used to it.
Pros of Guerlain Shalimar Parfum Initial Eau De Parfum:

Fragrance is amazing.
A mature yet sophisticated fragrance.
A little goes a long way.
Staying power of up to 12 hours.
Beautiful packaging.

Cons of Guerlain Shalimar Parfum Initial Eau De Parfum:

Expensive.
May induce headache in some people.
Not an everyday perfume.
Not travel friendly.

IMBB Rating:
4/5
Would I Recommend Guerlain Shalimar Parfum Initial Eau De Parfum?
Yes, I would recommend it to woman who love strong perfumes and mature fragrances.

Guerlain La Petite Robe Noire Black Perfecto Review 

Guerlain’s La Petite Robe Noire is the fragrance equivalent of the world’s coolest movie franchise. She’s a super hero, of course, ... bit too far, I agree, but it’s fair to say that La Petite Robe Noire has character in spades and Guerlain has done a fantastic job of taking the fruity floral genre and having fun with it. Each of the fragrances in La Petite Robe Noire’s wardrobe presents a fun twist on the signature smoky cherry accord that makes this Guerlain so cheeky and modern. Now with this latest interpretation, Guerlain are giving their fancy, fun loving signature fragrance (their modern signature, that is) a rocky edge.
Dubbed Black Perfecto, this La Petite Robe Noire is billed by Guerlain as an Eau Florale, possibly due to the fact that it showcases three rose materials; rose water, rose essence and ... black leather against a veritable patisserie of gourmand notes. Black Perfecto is so cool, so much fun and so very Guerlain it’s hard not to sniff it and smile. So if you love La Petite Robe Noire but just want MORE, ... date!

Universal bronzing shade
This is the best-selling shade in the Guerlain bronzing line: 03 Natural Brunettes. It warms up the complexion in seconds.
Coral shade
This coral shade is a pro ... the Terracotta bronzer comes houses in metal case decorated with a tropical design and engraved with the golden Terracotta and Guerlain signatures. A large mirror inside the cap allows for easy application and touch ups.
But what I love most about this design is the nod to Guerlain’s heritage. You’ll find an Art Deco design embossed onto the powder. The fanned motif was used often during the Era and it is an elegant touch.

インフィニティ アドバンスト モイスチュア コンセントレート 50ml・8,000円(税抜) 皮膚の水分保持能を改善し、肌環境を立て直す薬用保湿美容液です。バイオテクノロジーで抽出した美容成分を配合。厳選された美容成分がトータルで働きかけ、うるおいの土台から立て直すことで根本から美しさをつくりあげます。肌自身のうるおい力を高め、エイジングサインの気にならない理想的なハリ肌にみちびきます。浸透シャワー処方を採用。美容成分のうるおいをたっぷり抱えたまろやかなベースが、ハリのなさが気になる肌にもスーッと角層まで浸透。使用してすぐに、もちもちとした弾力とハリが実感できます。肌をやわらかくととのえ、次に使う化粧品のなじみを高め、効果を引き出します。心を豊かにうるおす 、フローラル ウッディのやさしい香りです。 付けかえ用 50ml 7,800円 (医薬部外品) アドバンスト モイスチュア コンセントレートの使用感 朝晩使っています。 2プッシュもすれば十分な量かと。 商品説明を読むとエイジングケア的な位置づけっぽいですが、使用感としては保湿美容液といった感じです。 パンと張った感じよりも、もっとみずみずしいというか水分を蓄えた肌っぽい感触になります。 化粧水ではなく美容液で保湿する 「保湿は化粧水ではなく美容液でするもの」というのはゲランのBAさんが教えてくれた話ですが、それ以来私は化粧水に対する期待値をすっかり下げてしまい(笑)。 それまで化粧水なんてさっぱりタイプ~しっとりタイプまで、2・3本重ね付けがデフォルトだったのですが、今はブースター使ったら化粧水は1本で済ませています。 とりあえず肌湿らせる程度で、あとは美容液に全部おまかせしてもいいかなと。 (B.Aのローションなんかは別格ですが) たぶん化粧水は「潤いを保つ」のではなく「潤いを与える」んでしょうね。 結局それを「蓄える」には美容液が必要なんじゃないかなと。 化粧水にフタの機能がないとすれば、当然の話しではあるのですが。 話がそれましたが、そんなわけで今現在私のお肌の水分を蓄えようと頑張ってくれているのはこの子だと思います。 インフィニティ  アドバンスト モイスチュア コンセントレート 50ml

Sempena Hari Peneroka 2017 yang disambut hari ini, sukacita saya umumkan 6 insentif bagi menghargai sumbangan dan jasa peneroka yang berdiri teguh bersama Felda. 

Pertama sekali, Kerajaan memperuntukkan RM519 juta bagi melupuskan hutang tanam semula berjumlah RM5,000 untuk setiap peneroka yang telah memilih untuk menanam semula melalui Felda.

Kedua, Kerajaan juga sentiasa prihatin terhadap keselesaan dan kebajikan peneroka Felda. Oleh itu, peneroka kini boleh membina lebih daripada 1 unit rumah dalam 1 tapak. Perkara ini telah dipersetujui oleh kerajaan negeri pada dasarnya.

Ketiga, Kerajaan juga akan memberi dana khas pelupusan lebihan hutang tanam semula sebanyak RM300 juta bagi tempoh 5 tahun bermula 2017 hingga 2021 bagi melupuskan hutang kos operasi melebihi jangkaan RM40,000. Ini bermakna jika hutang bagi kos operasi tanam semula adalah RM60,000, sebanyak RM20,000 akan dilupuskan menggunakan peruntukan dana khas ini.

Keempat, sebahagian baki pinjaman saham FGV juga akan dilupuskan selari dengan usaha ke arah tadbir urus dan integriti yang lebih mantap. Sehingga kini, seramai 77,934 peneroka yang sedang membayar pinjaman saham FGV akan dilupuskan baki pinjaman mereka dengan kadar ringgit ke ringgit manakala 1,626 peneroka yang telah habis bayar akan terima ganjaran tunai RM1,820. Inisiatif ini akan melibatkan peruntukan sebanyak RM128.1 juta.

Kelima, peneroka juga bakal menerima geran khas tanam semula dengan kadar RM7,500 setiap hektar bermula tahun 2017 hingga 2020 yang telah diluluskan oleh Lembaga Minyak Sawit Malaysia kepada Felda. Ini bakal melibatkan keluasan 24,280.31 hektar dengan peruntukan RM166.6 juta untuk 4 tahun akan datang.

Akhir sekali, peneroka-peneroka juga bakal menerima bayaran insentif khas bernilai RM5,000. Ini akan memanfaatkan 94,956 keluarga peneroka yang layak penuh dengan peruntukan sebanyak RM474.78 juta. Insya-Allah, pembayaran akan mula dibuat penghujung Ogos ini.

Mon Guerlain Mon Guerlain Perfume (50ml pictured)* | Mon Guerlain Shower Gel (200ml) | Mon Guerlain Body Lotion*I went to a meeting with a PR expecting to fall in love with a fragrance and instead fell ... liked the fragrance already – unless you’ve been hiding under a rock you’d be hard pressed to have missed Mon Guerlain, the newest perfume launch from the house of Guerlain which has Angelina Jolie as the star of the campaign. Guerlain placed themselves firmly on the fragrance map – with Mon Guerlain stands at the front of every major department store and grabbed everyone’s attention. The fragrance itself... well, I’ll get into that.I love a brand with history behind it, and that’s really where I’ve fallen for Guerlain – in its story. Guerlain started all the way back in 1828 – before Dior, before Chanel, the French had Guerlain. Despite the fact it’s a brand that arguably, until the stratospheric launch of Mon Guerlain, has been somewhat under the radar here in the UK, in France Guerlain is a renowned brand, an integral part of French history, and for me that’s probably most summed up in the fact that La Signature at the French Pavilion in EPCOT is an exclusively Guerlain store. Say what you will about Disney but the amount of thought they put into every aspect of the parks ... brand I can understand all the details of the shop even more.But back to the history – in 1853 Pierre-François-Pascal Guerlain, created Eau de Cologne Impériale for Empress Eugenie, to celebrate her marriage to Emperor Napoleon III. He decorated the bottle ... has 69 bees on it because there are 69 provences in France, and Empress Eugenie must have liked it because Guerlain went on to become ‘Her Majesty’s Patened Perfumer’. The bee icon features in the ceilings of Guerlain’s beautiful Champs-Elysees store – the lovely Harriet from Guerlain sent me these over to show you and, whilst they make look as light and airy as balloons those are ... bees from the ceiling, you can only begin to imagine how incredibly beautiful the rest of the store is. Jacques Guerlain – the third generation of the family to run the business was the Guerlain who claimed 68 Champs-Elysees as the House of Guerlain’s home. Work began in 1914, led by the architect Charles Mewès, who was also behind the Ritz Hotel in Paris, ... in those marble elements that have never been, and never will be, changed.As well as the marble the 68 Champs-Elysee Guerlain store (which incidentally is the biggest beauty store in the world dedicated to one brand!) is also home to a unique Guerlain experience – where you can have your own scent completely custom blended. And as you would expect, that comes at ... one of the most fantastic and indulgent purchases ever, is maybe something a little closer to being affordable for the Guerlain fan.Which brings me back to Guerlain fragrances – and in particular the reason I went to the meeting in the first place. Mon Guerlain is beautiful – very feminine, very soft. I actually was really surprised by how much I liked it because I ... do light, but somehow I really like this fragrance. And part of the reason for that is probably The Guerlinaid.The Guerlainaid – doesn’t it sound wonderfully straight from Harry Potter? Mystical, magical and intriguing – perfect for a brand with so ... so much beauty behind it. The Guerlinade is compromised of 6 ingredients and those ingredients form the basis of all Guerlain perfumes. They are Calabrian Bergamont, Tuscan Iris, Bulgarian Rose, South American Tonka Bean, Vanilla and Grandiflorum and Sambac Jasime.Those spices mixed with the florals, with that hint of citrus cut through the two main florals in Mon Guerlain’s notes. Those are Carla Lavender, which gives a fresh note to the fragrance and as an ingredient is 50 times ... not usually the biggest fan of Jasmine but this is balanced out for me by the other notes. Such is Guerlain’s dedication to their perfume that the only use Jasmine which has been picked at a certain time in the morning, ... and now there are two crops in the world - one of which belongs to Chanel, and the other to Guerlain - which means these are the only two houses who will be able to produce fragrances using it.Lastly it counts

A NEW SCENT: MON GUERLAIN EAU DE PARFUM 
Fun fact. Did you know Guerlain made the first ever lipstick Ne m’oubliez pas in 1871 and the first compact bronzing powder (Terracotta) in 1984? Who knew eh?! KissKiss la nueva colección de Guerlain No hay nada que nos guste más que una barra de labios, confesar conmigo: "nunca tenemos suficientes", por este motivo la colección de Guerlain esta temporada es sorprendente y de esas colecciones que gustan a todas, de las que nunca te cansas, de las que no pasan de moda, atemporal.Los labios son los protagonistas indiscutibles de la nueva colección de Guerlain, barras de labios, labiales líquidos y dos paletas de labios.Cuando terminéis de leer este post, vais a necesitarlo todo, avisadas estáis...KissKiss Matte: la barra de labios (38,70 euros)El primer mate hidratante y densificante de Guerlain.Ofrece un color intenso como la mejor barra de labios, al tiempo es confortable con los labios como un bálsamo.Su fórmula ... ofrecen alta cobertura con buena pigmentación, todo ello en un estuche de lujo, como caracteriza a la firma.Intense Liquid Matte Guerlain (35,10 euros)Creo que este tipo de color para labios líquidos han sido la revolución de las últimas temporadas, me declaro ... los Rouge Dior Líquidos, son todo lo que busco en una barra de labios.Este es el primer Liquid Lipstick  de Guerlain, de acabado mate, confortable gracias a su formulación con ácido hialurónico.7 tonos con gran cobertura y pigmentación.Paleta KissKiss From Paris ... incluyen 3 texturas cremosas que subliman los labios, perfilan el contorno y aplican colorAhora decidme, ¿no lo necesitáis todo?¡Un aplauso Guerlain, una colección imprescindible!
